Early Access Review

Hi there, i'd like to share my own XP about this game:

Pros:     Graphics is just brilliant (of course if your PC meet recommended specs);
Sountrack is also good (it doesn't annoy you even after 10h of playtime :-)
Phisics is good but sometimes Mobs go though the stones and spawn too often;
Maps are simply huge (you'll never get enough time to explore them all);
You can host your own server! but Windows based only :-(
Cons:     Looks like the whole map loads into RAMM when you start the game thus if you have a noisy PC it will hurt;
Weird but I didn't find how to control sounds volume and graphics quality;
System of gaining XP for you hero (first 4 lvls are gained fast but then you are tired of killing mobs 'coz each lvl you gain the less XP you get (you have to find Mobs with a lvl higher than your own);
Craft receipts (Blueprints) spawned random from killed mobs and you never know what you get;
You have to cut down too much trees (GreanPeace doesn't approve);
Too high system reqs and no 32bit OS suppport (it leads to small amount players and dedicated servers are empty);
P.S.: Campfire in a wooden house is supposed to destroy building but it doesn't :-)
